Pre-Game Insights: The Boston Celtics have hit the ground running with five wins from their first six games.

Jayson Tatum led the team with 32 points, 11 rebounds, and three assists, Jaylen Brown added 25 points with six rebounds and five assists while Derrick White chipped in with 17 points and five assists.
The Celtics shot 47 percent from the field and 13 of 42 from the 3-point line as they set the tone with 40 points in the first quarter to take an early 17-point lead.
The Hornets came back to cut the lead to just one point before the Celtics went on a pivotal 7-0 run in the fourth quarter to pull away in the end.
The Hornets have lost three of their last four games overall.

LaMelo Ball led the team with 31 points on 12 of 25 shooting, Tre Mann added 23 points with five assists off the bench while Miles Bridges chipped in with 14 points, seven rebounds, and three assists.
As a team, the Hornets shot 46 percent from the field and 19 of 48 from the 3-point line as they exploded for 42 points in the second quarter to claw back from an early deficit.
